
[1]prettiness

   PRETTINESS, n. prit'tiness. [from pretty.]

   1. Diminutive beauty; a pleasing form without stateliness or dignity;
   as the prettiness of the face; the prettiness of a bird or other small
   animal; the prettiness of dress.

   2. Neatness and taste displayed on small objects; as the prettiness of
   a flower bed.

   3. Decency of manners; pleasing propriety without dignity or elevation;
   as the prettiness of a child'd behavior.
